text: "You're Makin' Me High" is the lead single from the American singer Toni Braxton's second studio album, Secrets (1996). This song is medium-tempo, so not very fast or very slow. It was made by Babyface and Bryce Wilson. It came out the United States as a double A-side with the song "Let It Flow". Brandy and Dallas Austin were going to write the words to it at first. title: You're Makin' Me High
